real_commentary: KICKOFF:  THE SECOND EURO 2024 SEMI-FINAL IS UNDERWAY!
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The first half begins. Euro 2024 Semi-Final between Netherlands and England!

real_commentary: Malen immediately tries a run in behind but the Dutchman is caught offside.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Declan Rice (England) on Donyell Malen (Netherlands). Free kick awarded.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  The effervescent Simons charges forward on the right and tries to thread a pass into Malen, but Guehi does enough to shield the ball back to Jordan Pickford.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Nathan Aké (Netherlands) on Marc Guehi (England). Free kick awarded on the right wing.

real_commentary: England settle into a nice period of possession and Phil Foden wins a free kick off of Jerdy Schouten.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Nathan Aké (Netherlands) on Marc Guehi (England). Free kick awarded on the right wing.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  England quickly go down the other end and Saka floats in a cross to the back stick, but Stefan de Vrij is there to clear.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Declan Rice (England) on Stefan de Vrij (Netherlands). Free kick awarded in the defensive half.

real_commentary: GOAL!  NETHERLANDS 1-0 ENGLAND (SIMONS)
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Xavi Simons puts the Netherlands on the scoreboard with a right-footed shot from the edge of the box. Netherlands 0, England 0.

real_commentary: GOAL!  AND THAT IS WHAT XAVI SIMONS DOES. THE NETHERLANDS LEAD IN THE SEVENTH MINUTE.
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Xavi Simons puts the Netherlands on the scoreboard with a right-footed shot from the edge of the box. Netherlands 0, England 0.

real_commentary: Kieran Trippier goes for the long ball over the top to Bellingham - back in Dortmund territory - but it rolls harmlessly through to Bart Verbruggen.
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Xavi Simons puts the Netherlands on the scoreboard with a right-footed shot from the edge of the box. Netherlands 0, England 0.

real_commentary: Who would have had Simons out-muscling Rice down before the game? Certainly not me, but that was terrific work from the Dutchman.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Jude Bellingham (England) is down with an injury, receiving medical attention.

real_commentary: Foden takes it but his Manchester City teammate Ake heads clear.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Matthijs de Ligt (Netherlands) on Kieran Trippier (England) at the edge of the box.

real_commentary: Trippier takes this one and finds Rice at the back post. The Arsenal man tries to cut back for a teammate but can only find the boot of Van Dijk.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Harry Kane's right footed shot from the edge of the box denied by Bart Verbruggen.

real_commentary: SAVE!  HARRY KANE HAS A SHOT!
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Denzel Dumfries (Netherlands) receives a yellow card for a foul on Harry Kane (England).

real_commentary: SHOT!  Kane now fires over the top after a quick break and brilliant work from Saka!
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Denzel Dumfries (Netherlands) receives a yellow card for a foul on Harry Kane (England).

real_commentary: GOAL!  NETHERLANDS 1-1 ENGLAND (KANE)
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Netherlands 0, England 1. Harry Kane scores with a right-footed shot from the centre of the box.

real_commentary: GOAL!  Kane makes no mistake! Verbruggen dives the right way, but Kane's penalty is just too perfect.
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Netherlands 0, England 1. Harry Kane scores with a right-footed shot from the centre of the box.

real_commentary: There will certainly be some debate about the awarding of the penalty - I initially didn't think it was, but upon seeing a replay, Dumfries did go in with his studs.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Netherlands dominating play, controlling possession for the last two minutes.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  WHAT. A. CLEARANCE!!!!
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Phil Foden's right footed shot from the six yard box denied by Bart Verbruggen.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  Mainoo and Foden link up brilliantly as the latter prods the ball towards goal from a tight angle, and his toe-poke beats Verbruggen but Dumfries is there to stop the ball right on the line!
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Bart Verbruggen (Netherlands) is down with an injury, receiving medical attention.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  Mainoo and Foden link up brilliantly as the latter prods the ball towards goal from a tight angle, and his toe-poke beats Verbruggen but Dumfries is there to stop the ball right on the line!
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Injury concern for England as Jordan Pickford is down.

real_commentary: At the risk of jinxing it, this is by far England's best performance at Euro 2024 so far. The Dutch living incredibly dangerously and just unable to contain Southgate's inspired team.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Netherlands dominating midfield, holding 100% possession, mainly through Denzel Dumfries.

real_commentary: SHOT!  The Netherlands go on one of their quick breaks, but a combination of Walker and Guehi denies Malen as the Netherlands win their first corner of the game.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Blocked] Attempt blocked. Donyell Malen's left footed shot from the center of the box denied by Marc Guehi.

real_commentary: OFF THE BAR!  Dumfries is absolutely everywhere tonight!
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Denzel Dumfries hits the post with a header from the center of the box!

real_commentary: OFF THE BAR!  OH MY GOODNESS!
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt hits the post! Phil Foden's left-footed shot from the edge of the box.

real_commentary: Two woodwork hits in two minutes, a Kane penalty and a Simons stunner - this has been an utterly breathless start in Dortmund.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Tijjani Reijnders (Netherlands) on Phil Foden (England) in the attacking third.

real_commentary: A chance for a breather now, though, as Memphis Depay is down and needs treatment.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Injury concern for the Netherlands as Memphis Depay goes down.

real_commentary: A chance for a breather now, though, as Memphis Depay is down and needs treatment.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Injury concern for England as Jordan Pickford is down.

real_commentary: NETHERLANDS SUB
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for the Netherlands. Memphis Depay is replaced by Joey Veerman due to injury.

real_commentary: Bellingham goes down under pressure from Schouten but Zwayer is not interested.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating play, controlling midfield with 67.7% possession. Jude Bellingham pivotal in the last 2 minutes.

real_commentary: SHOT!  Just as I say that, Foden again tries to pick out the far corner from 25 yards, but Verbruggen - at full stretch - makes the save and holds onto the ball.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Phil Foden's left-footed strike from the edge of the box denied by Bart Verbruggen.

real_commentary: The Netherlands' shape already looks more rigid since the introduction of Veerman. England now reverting to a bit of slow build-up in front of an orange wall.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Phil Foden's left-footed strike from the edge of the box denied by Bart Verbruggen.

real_commentary: SHOT!  Mainoo - who has been exceptional so far - robs Gakpo and lets fly from range, but his strike smacks Nathan Ake and goes out for a throw.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Blocked] Attempt blocked. Kobbie Mainoo's right-footed shot from the edge of the box denied by Nathan Aké.

real_commentary: Approaching half time, England can pat themselves on the back and then some. Whatever they had for breakfast at their hotel this morning has gone down a treat.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England asserting dominance, controlling midfield with 100% possession. John Stones highly active with 12 events.

real_commentary: Southgate's men also ending the first 45 the better as Trippier gets down the left, but his cross is straight into Verbruggen's hands.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Even midfield battle continues, England slightly edging possession as Nathan Aké leads with six events.

real_commentary: Three minutes added on.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Even midfield battle continues, England slightly edging possession as Nathan Aké leads with six events.

real_commentary: KICKOFF:  The Netherlands get us back underway.
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The second half is underway in this Semi-Final clash!

real_commentary: KICKOFF:  The Netherlands get us back underway.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for Netherlands. Wout Weghorst replaces Donyell Malen for tactical reasons.

real_commentary: KICKOFF:  The Netherlands get us back underway.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for England. Luke Shaw replaces Kieran Trippier for tactical reasons.

real_commentary: Let him know you're there and all that.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Netherlands on John Stones (England) in midfield.

real_commentary: England quickly take control of the ball and Saka gets in behind Ake, but there is nobody there to receive his cutback.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Luke Shaw (England) on Xavi Simons (Netherlands). Free kick awarded in midfield.

real_commentary: The offside flag is up against England, but it's been another bright start from the men in white.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Bukayo Saka (England) on Virgil van Dijk (Netherlands) in the defensive half.

real_commentary: Patience is the name of the game right now for England, as Koeman's side have well and truly tightened up defensively.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England asserting dominance with 100% possession, controlling midfield play.

real_commentary: Mainoo has been an absolute force defensively and stands up to Simons on the right, before Tijjani Reijnders sends the ball straight out of play when looking for Dumfries.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Netherlands in control with 93.3% possession, dominating the midfield.

real_commentary: I suspected the chances might dry up a bit when Koeman beefed up his midfield with the introduction of Veerman, and it has panned out exactly that way.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England asserting dominance with 100% possession, controlling the midfield.

real_commentary: England still dominating possession but finding it far more difficult to penetrate the Orange wall.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating possession with 68.4%, controlling the midfield for 3 minutes.

real_commentary: Koeman's men break quickly - surprise surprise - and Veerman tries to find Weghorst at the back post, but he overcooks his outswinging cross.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominant in midfield, controlling play for the last five minutes. 77.8% possession.

real_commentary: This now feels too reminiscent of England's first four matches at the tournament, struggling to find gaps in a compact backline, but the Dutch are not giving Pickford anything to think about either.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Declan Rice (England) on Stefan de Vrij (Netherlands). Free kick awarded in the defensive half.

real_commentary: SAVE!  Veerman swings in a free kick for the Netherlands after Simons draws a foul by the dugouts, and Van Dijk gets his toe to it, forcing Pickford into a good reaction save!
our_sequence_commentary: [Shots] Pressure from the Netherlands, two attempts in quick succession. Van Dijk's shot saved, Dumfries heads off target.

real_commentary: SHOT!  From the resulting corner, Dumfries wins the header again, but he cannot keep this effort down.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Wout Weghorst (Netherlands) on John Stones (England) in midfield.

real_commentary: Things are starting to happen for the Netherlands now, as Gakpo delivers a dangerous ball from the left, which Pickford has to punch behind for a corner.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Netherlands dominating midfield with 100% possession, led by Jerdy Schouten's involvement.

real_commentary: Ake wins the header but Zwayer had spotted something that he didn't like. England free kick.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for Netherlands, delivered by Joey Veerman. Conceded by Jordan Pickford.

real_commentary: Time to mutter the dreaded two words, extra time?
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Netherlands controlling the game with 100% possession, Xavi Simons pivotal in midfield.

real_commentary: YELLOW CARD!  Bellingham and De Vrij go in for a 50-50, but it is the England man who is penalised. Yellow card from Zwayer.
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Jude Bellingham (England) shown a yellow card for a foul on Stefan de Vrij (Netherlands).

real_commentary: Saka down on the right after taking Ake's hand in his face, but no interest from the referee.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Free kick awarded to Netherlands after a foul by Marc Guehi on Wout Weghorst.

real_commentary: Surely both managers will be starting to think about changes pretty soon. Just the one alteration from Southgate, two from Koeman - one enforced.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Netherlands in control, dominating the attacking third for 2 minutes. Joey Veerman very active.

real_commentary: SAVE!  Simons connects with a volley, but his connection is anything but clean - one bounce into the ground and Pickford gathers.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating possession, controlling the midfield with 100%. Luke Shaw highly active.

real_commentary: Cole Palmer and Ollie Watkins about to emerge for England.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating midfield with 100% possession, led by Declan Rice for 2 minutes.

real_commentary: DISALLOWED GOAL!  SAKA HAS THE BALL IN THE BACK OF THE NET, BUT THE OFFSIDE FLAG IS UP!
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating midfield with 100% possession, led by Declan Rice for 2 minutes.

real_commentary: DISALLOWED GOAL!  Foden slips in Walker down the right, and the Manchester City man cuts back for Saka to guide home a brilliant first-time finish, but the right-back had just gone a bit too early.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Double change for England. Ollie Watkins and Phil Foden replace Harry Kane.

real_commentary: DISALLOWED GOAL!  Foden slips in Walker down the right, and the Manchester City man cuts back for Saka to guide home a brilliant first-time finish, but the right-back had just gone a bit too early.

our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Bukayo Saka (England) on Virgil van Dijk (Netherlands). Free kick awarded in defensive half.

real_commentary: Some beautiful play from Reijnders down the left, but Guehi stands up tall and takes the full force of Weghorst's 6ft 6in frame to snuff out the attack.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Kyle Walker (England) on Cody Gakpo (Netherlands) near the box.

our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Virgil van Dijk (Netherlands) shown a yellow card for a late challenge.
